lsb_release a = for checking the version of linux


TO INSTALL R
Press Ctrl+Alt+T to open the Terminal;
then execute sudo apt-get update; after that,
run sudo apt-get install r-base;
sudo apt-get install r-base-dev


TO DOWNLOAD R STUDIO
just download it from the website

TO INSTALL POSGRESQL
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib
sudo -i -u postgres or sudo -u postgres psql

psql

TO quit
\q

use repository only when needed(ONLY TO CHECK THE VERSION)

deb http://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt/ YOUR_UBUNTU_VERSION_HERE-pgdg main


wget --quiet -O - https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc | sudo apt-key add -
sudo apt-get update

to install r packages

deb https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/linux/ubuntu disco-cran35/

TO UPDATE THE PACKAGES
 
sudo apt-get build-dep r-cran-foo OR any other cran names

